          "id": "arc-1513a6dc9ed93462",
          "text": "In mice, a certain species displays incomplete dominance in coat coloring. The offspring of a black (BB) mouse and a white (bb) mouse are gray (Bb) mice. A cross between two gray mice will most likely produce offspring with which percent of coat colors?",
